With the statement released yesterday by the Federal Bureau of Investigation (FBI), which indicted about 88 Nigerians, the Chairman/Chief Executive Officer of the Nigerian Diaspora Commission, Abike Dabiri-Erewa, Friday asked those accused of fraudulent activities to submit themselves to the American authorities, noting that Nigerian government would extradite them if they fail to do so.<img class="size-full wp-image-1230647 aligncenter" src="https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Abike-Dabiri-Erewa.jpg?resize=640%2C872&#038;ssl=1" alt="BBNaija" width="640" height="872" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Abike-Dabiri-Erewa.jpg?w=1500&amp;ssl=1 1500w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Abike-Dabiri-Erewa.jpg?resize=220%2C300&amp;ssl=1 220w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Abike-Dabiri-Erewa.jpg?resize=768%2C1047&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Abike-Dabiri-Erewa.jpg?resize=751%2C1024&amp;ssl=1 751w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Abike-Dabiri-Erewa.jpg?resize=43%2C58&amp;ssl=1 43w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Abike-Dabiri-Erewa.jpg?resize=142%2C194&amp;ssl=1 142w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Abike-Dabiri-Erewa.jpg?resize=95%2C130&amp;ssl=1 95w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Abike-Dabiri-Erewa.jpg?resize=560%2C763&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Abike-Dabiri-Erewa.jpg?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> In her statement Abike utterly frowned at the incident, noting that those accused are still innocent pending courts pronouncement against them. Her words, “We acknowledge the fact that accusation does not mean guilt, and we hope that all the accused will be given fair and speedy trial. Buhari’s Ministerial Inauguration, A poor parade – PDP(Opens in a new browser tab) “We also ask those accused in Nigeria to voluntarily turn themselves in to American authorities to clear their names without which the Nigerian government should extradite them if relevant international treaties between the two governments are invoked. “While such actions ultimately have negative effect on the image of the country, the commission, however, reiterates as it has always done, that the actions of a few Nigerians involved in criminal activities is not and can never be what the majority of Nigerians represent.” Vanguard It would be recalled that the inter-agency panel last week called the bluff of the American government over the failure of the FBI to assist the panel corroborate the confessions of some prime suspects during interrogation which is key to their being nailed. June 19, 2009 In "Headlines" THE Federal Government, yesterday, made good its pledge to seek the assistance of foreign bomb experts to get to the root of New Year Eve bomb blast at the Mammy Market of the Mogadishu Cantonment, Abuja which claimed four lives and injured several others as United States Federal Bureau of… January 3, 2011 In "Headlines" Yusifiyya Movement, also known as Boko Haram, yesterday, said it attacked the United Nations (UN) building in Abuja because United States (US) and the UN are supporting the Federal Government to persecute Muslims in Nigeria. August 28, 2011 In "Headlines"